  <brief_title>Influence of Oxytocin on Romantic Jealousy</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>University of Electronic Science and Technology of China</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>University of Electronic Science and Technology of China</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim is to evoke romantic jealousy between couples and investigate whether oxytocin has
      effect on it.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      In a double-blind, between- subject placebo (PLC) controlled design,investigators plan to
      test the effect of intranasal oxytocin on romantic jealousy evoked by the Imaginary of
      Partner's Infidelity Task and Cyberball Game in romantically attached subjects.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
